The paper deals with the learning of interpretable models for classification, specifically Boolean rules in either DNF or CNF. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of integer programming and column generation for efficient search suggests a focus on optimization (cs.DM) and algorithm design (cs.SI). Finally, the emphasis on interpretability and simplicity in the learned rules may also relate to work in computational ethics (cs.CE).
